<p>This should be thread-safe, am I right? Is there maybe a better way?</p>  <pre><code>Imports System.Threading  Public Class ApplicationIdleHelper     Private Shared lastInputTicks As Long      Public Shared Sub SetLastInputTime(dt As DateTime)         Interlocked.Exchange(lastInputTicks, dt.Ticks)     End Sub      Public Shared Function GetIdleTime() As Integer         Return (Now - New DateTime(Interlocked.Read(lastInputTicks))).TotalSeconds     End Function End Class </code></pre>  <p>In my application I'm setting the <code>lastInputTicks</code> value with the method <code>SetLastInputTime</code> in the <code>PreFilterMessage</code> event. In some other <code>Threads</code> I have to check this variable. I do this by calling <code>GetIdleTime</code>, but now I'm not sure, if this is thread-safe or I can get in trouble.</p>  <p>Thank you in advance!</p>